1
00:01:36,750 --> 00:01:40,940
[Footprints of Change]

2
00:01:41,390 --> 00:01:43,890
[Episode 22]

3
00:01:45,570 --> 00:01:46,530
Slow down.

4
00:01:53,360 --> 00:01:57,090
[Junlong Company]

5
00:01:57,090 --> 00:01:59,009
You said I'm treating, right?

6
00:02:04,840 --> 00:02:06,590
I'd like scrambled eggs with tomato

7
00:02:06,590 --> 00:02:08,470
and some twice-cooked pork.

8
00:02:08,630 --> 00:02:09,070
Okay.

9
00:02:09,250 --> 00:02:10,050
Okay, thanks.

10
00:02:15,700 --> 00:02:17,710
So this thing's called a computer, huh?

11
00:02:17,710 --> 00:02:18,760
I bought it 6 months ago.

12
00:02:18,760 --> 00:02:19,960
No one's ever used it.

13
00:02:23,400 --> 00:02:25,050
Alright, Professor Xiang.

14
00:02:25,490 --> 00:02:26,990
What brings you here today?

15
00:02:26,990 --> 00:02:27,710
Let's talk.

16
00:02:31,520 --> 00:02:33,470
You set your office here.

17
00:02:34,280 --> 00:02:35,940
Aren't you afraid of bad luck?

18
00:02:37,430 --> 00:02:39,150
Business depends on brains,

19
00:02:39,150 --> 00:02:40,310
nothing else.

20
00:02:41,310 --> 00:02:42,120
Besides,

21
00:02:42,500 --> 00:02:43,829
when I rented this place,

22
00:02:43,829 --> 00:02:45,829
that incident hadn't happened yet.

23
00:02:46,079 --> 00:02:47,940
No, seriously—tell me the truth.

24
00:02:48,310 --> 00:02:50,600
With so many fancy
office buildings around,

25
00:02:50,600 --> 00:02:51,930
why'd you pick this one?

26
00:02:52,520 --> 00:02:53,980
Fei had his accident here.

27
00:02:54,120 --> 00:02:55,520
Doesn't that bother you?

28
00:02:56,550 --> 00:02:58,040
I used to be a scholar too.

29
00:02:58,280 --> 00:02:59,710
I need a cultural atmosphere.

30
00:02:59,710 --> 00:03:00,710
When you entered this room,

31
00:03:00,710 --> 00:03:02,640
didn't you feel the cultural vibe?

32
00:03:04,190 --> 00:03:05,800
I didn't smell any culture.

33
00:03:06,580 --> 00:03:08,140
But I did smell dog.

34
00:03:09,360 --> 00:03:11,030
Your nose is sharper than a dog's.

35
00:03:11,030 --> 00:03:13,290
There actually is one, believe it or not.

36
00:03:13,450 --> 00:03:14,550
Alright, enough joking around.

37
00:03:14,550 --> 00:03:15,370
Let's talk business.

38
00:03:15,370 --> 00:03:15,970
So,

39
00:03:16,310 --> 00:03:16,840
how are things?

40
00:03:16,840 --> 00:03:18,170
What are your plans now?

41
00:03:19,920 --> 00:03:21,520
I don't know what to do.

42
00:03:22,440 --> 00:03:23,200
Normally,

43
00:03:24,040 --> 00:03:24,700
I could go to

44
00:03:24,950 --> 00:03:25,680
a newspaper,

45
00:03:25,800 --> 00:03:26,690
a magazine,

46
00:03:26,710 --> 00:03:28,110
or a research institute.

47
00:03:31,140 --> 00:03:32,870
You were a prominent reporter.

48
00:03:33,240 --> 00:03:34,570
You know a lot of people.

49
00:03:35,030 --> 00:03:36,690
Give me some advice, will you?

50
00:03:39,190 --> 00:03:40,800
The idea that mindset determines destiny

51
00:03:40,800 --> 00:03:42,360
is absolutely true.

52
00:03:42,560 --> 00:03:43,240
Do you realize

53
00:03:43,240 --> 00:03:45,190
everywhere's downsizing these days?

54
00:03:45,190 --> 00:03:46,680
So, Professor Xiang,

55
00:03:47,010 --> 00:03:48,470
have you won a Nobel Prize?

56
00:03:48,870 --> 00:03:50,750
Or do you have some patented invention?

57
00:03:50,750 --> 00:03:52,000
You have neither.

58
00:03:52,590 --> 00:03:54,030
All you can do is writing.

59
00:03:54,030 --> 00:03:55,710
Is that worth anything nowadays?

60
00:03:55,710 --> 00:03:56,560
Not at all.

61
00:03:57,890 --> 00:03:58,890
And you know what,

62
00:03:59,240 --> 00:04:00,120
recently,

63
00:04:00,120 --> 00:04:00,910
a friend of mine who works

64
00:04:00,910 --> 00:04:02,430
at the Ministry of Education told me,

65
00:04:02,430 --> 00:04:04,630
a new policy is about to be implemented.

66
00:04:04,800 --> 00:04:05,840
After it takes effect,

67
00:04:05,840 --> 00:04:07,800
college graduates
won't be assigned jobs anymore.

68
00:04:07,800 --> 00:04:09,730
Do you understand what that means?

69
00:04:10,110 --> 00:04:12,270
To enter any government
agency or institution,

70
00:04:12,270 --> 00:04:14,270
you'll have to
take exams yourself.

71
00:04:14,300 --> 00:04:15,370
Someone like me, Yan Jun,

72
00:04:15,370 --> 00:04:16,670
who's got some influence, right?

73
00:04:16,670 --> 00:04:17,579
It's useless.

74
00:04:18,750 --> 00:04:21,750
So you're telling me
a university lecturer like me...

75
00:04:23,500 --> 00:04:24,940
really has no way out?

76
00:04:25,480 --> 00:04:26,860
That's the reality for you right now.

77
00:04:26,860 --> 00:04:27,990
What did you expect?

78
00:04:34,640 --> 00:04:35,310
Chuan,

79
00:04:35,780 --> 00:04:36,980
I've told you before,

80
00:04:37,630 --> 00:04:39,920
you need to adapt to
the trends of this era.

81
00:04:39,920 --> 00:04:41,630
You need to keep up with the times.

82
00:04:41,630 --> 00:04:42,600
Shift your mindset.

83
00:04:42,600 --> 00:04:43,460
Think about it.

84
00:04:43,950 --> 00:04:44,880
What do you mean?

85
00:04:47,480 --> 00:04:49,080
To go into business like you?

86
00:04:49,920 --> 00:04:50,950
Why not?

87
00:04:51,070 --> 00:04:52,190
But I don't know how.

88
00:04:52,190 --> 00:04:53,870
I'll teach you.

89
00:04:55,530 --> 00:04:57,330
Our company is hiring right now.

90
00:04:57,480 --> 00:04:59,070
But Chuan, if you join,

91
00:04:59,510 --> 00:05:01,240
I'm not making you my employee.

92
00:05:01,310 --> 00:05:03,240
The two of us would be partners.

93
00:05:03,800 --> 00:05:06,730
I'm offering you
the position of Creative Director.

94
00:05:06,770 --> 00:05:08,170
And the salary will be...

95
00:05:11,310 --> 00:05:12,110
2,000 yuan.

96
00:05:12,950 --> 00:05:14,380
After all these years as friends

97
00:05:14,380 --> 00:05:15,150
and classmates,

98
00:05:15,150 --> 00:05:16,680
I'm being generous, right?

99
00:05:16,830 --> 00:05:17,870
Now it's up to you.

100
00:05:18,360 --> 00:05:19,220
What do you say?

101
00:05:25,020 --> 00:05:26,820
Doesn't your company sell dogs?

102
00:05:27,790 --> 00:05:29,790
Why do you need a Creative Director?

103
00:05:30,070 --> 00:05:32,190
We can be creative with dogs too.

104
00:05:32,620 --> 00:05:33,770
Where do these dogs

105
00:05:34,950 --> 00:05:36,159
come from?

106
00:05:36,430 --> 00:05:37,760
What's their pedigree?

107
00:05:38,040 --> 00:05:40,190
Why are they worth that much money?

108
00:05:40,430 --> 00:05:41,830
Someone's got to tell that story.

109
00:05:41,830 --> 00:05:43,480
That's where you come in.

110
00:05:45,630 --> 00:05:46,560
I see.

111
00:05:47,190 --> 00:05:48,870
So at future class reunions,

112
00:05:49,600 --> 00:05:50,950
those of us who stayed at the university

113
00:05:50,950 --> 00:05:53,010
can say we're supported by the state,

114
00:05:53,480 --> 00:05:54,680
while you can only say

115
00:05:54,909 --> 00:05:56,370
you're supported by dogs.

116
00:05:56,710 --> 00:05:57,510
You know what,

117
00:05:58,409 --> 00:06:00,830
my neighbor used to have
this exact same dog.

118
00:06:00,830 --> 00:06:02,690
It actually looked a bit like you.

119
00:06:02,770 --> 00:06:03,990
Mainly because you both bark a lot,

120
00:06:03,990 --> 00:06:06,190
and honestly, you two even sound alike.

121
00:06:08,830 --> 00:06:09,760
Xiang Beichuan,

122
00:06:11,210 --> 00:06:13,090
what you're saying right now

123
00:06:13,670 --> 00:06:16,480
only proves—
you can't have it, so you mock it.

124
00:06:16,940 --> 00:06:19,200
It just shows you're jealous of my money.

125
00:06:19,240 --> 00:06:21,500
Do you think your words
can hurt me at all?

126
00:06:21,530 --> 00:06:24,330
Can you stop me from making money?

127
00:06:24,360 --> 00:06:25,120
Can you?

128
00:06:25,360 --> 00:06:26,160
Since you can't,

129
00:06:26,160 --> 00:06:27,800
why keep saying these things?

130
00:06:27,800 --> 00:06:28,560
It never ends.

131
00:06:28,560 --> 00:06:30,000
Always poking where it hurts.

132
00:06:30,000 --> 00:06:30,420
Just...

133
00:06:30,420 --> 00:06:31,480
speaking without any boundaries.

134
00:06:31,480 --> 00:06:32,470
Is this how you treat people?

135
00:06:32,470 --> 00:06:33,270
Is this what being educated means to you?

136
00:06:33,270 --> 00:06:34,700
Is this how you handle things?

137
00:06:34,700 --> 00:06:35,380
What...

138
00:06:35,710 --> 00:06:37,200
What's wrong with you?

139
00:06:38,000 --> 00:06:39,040
Why are you actually getting mad?

140
00:06:39,040 --> 00:06:39,680
I...

141
00:06:39,680 --> 00:06:41,120
Shouldn't I be mad?

142
00:06:41,120 --> 00:06:42,240
Shouldn't I be?

143
00:06:42,240 --> 00:06:43,600
If you were a dog, wouldn't you be mad?

144
00:06:43,600 --> 00:06:44,390
Well, I...

145
00:06:44,390 --> 00:06:45,790
I was just stating facts.

146
00:06:47,960 --> 00:06:49,420
Mr. Yan, here's your food.

147
00:06:50,870 --> 00:06:51,930
Put it on the table.

148
00:06:59,000 --> 00:07:01,240
Let's not waste time on useless talk.

149
00:07:02,040 --> 00:07:03,240
Your current problem

150
00:07:03,870 --> 00:07:05,040
is because of what happened with Fei,

151
00:07:05,040 --> 00:07:06,450
you owe the university a lot of money,

152
00:07:06,450 --> 00:07:06,970
right?

153
00:07:08,160 --> 00:07:09,390
From your 2,000 yuan salary each month,

154
00:07:09,390 --> 00:07:11,040
I'll deduct part to repay the university.

155
00:07:11,040 --> 00:07:12,120
You can keep the rest.

156
00:07:12,120 --> 00:07:13,320
What will your job be?

157
00:07:14,830 --> 00:07:15,470
Besides

158
00:07:15,690 --> 00:07:17,420
handling the promotion

159
00:07:17,660 --> 00:07:19,100
of my dogs and such,

160
00:07:19,560 --> 00:07:21,680
you'll also need to take their photos.

161
00:07:21,680 --> 00:07:22,950
Before taking photos

162
00:07:22,950 --> 00:07:24,870
you need to wash it thoroughly.

163
00:07:24,950 --> 00:07:26,980
The fur must be shiny

164
00:07:27,000 --> 00:07:28,120
and have texture.

165
00:07:30,480 --> 00:07:31,950
Just like your hair—

166
00:07:32,150 --> 00:07:34,159
not a single stray hair out of place.

167
00:07:34,159 --> 00:07:35,870
That's the standard. Got it?

168
00:07:36,240 --> 00:07:37,430
If that's clear to you,

169
00:07:37,430 --> 00:07:38,830
start work tomorrow.

170
00:07:43,360 --> 00:07:44,090
Mr. Yan.

171
00:07:45,000 --> 00:07:46,159
I can't do this job.

172
00:07:46,830 --> 00:07:48,630
You'd better find someone else.

173
00:07:49,360 --> 00:07:51,280
I'm going to the job market right now.

174
00:07:51,280 --> 00:07:52,270
I refuse to believe

175
00:07:52,270 --> 00:07:54,000
that I can't find a writing job.

176
00:07:54,070 --> 00:07:55,830
If you can find a job

177
00:07:55,830 --> 00:07:57,510
that pays 2,000 yuan a month
at the job market,

178
00:07:57,510 --> 00:07:59,040
then I, Yan Jun, am that dog!

179
00:07:59,870 --> 00:08:00,460
Fine.

180
00:08:19,920 --> 00:08:20,720
I'm leaving.

181
00:08:24,820 --> 00:08:26,990
[Shanghai Textile Industry Bureau]

182
00:08:35,669 --> 00:08:36,360
Ye.

183
00:08:36,840 --> 00:08:37,630
Come here.

184
00:08:37,840 --> 00:08:39,440
I have something to tell you.

185
00:08:41,600 --> 00:08:42,400
Director Jin,

186
00:08:43,630 --> 00:08:45,160
why don't I see Director Yu?

187
00:08:45,170 --> 00:08:46,240
Director Yu?

188
00:08:46,960 --> 00:08:48,360
You know your case

189
00:08:48,360 --> 00:08:49,440
is extremely serious

190
00:08:49,440 --> 00:08:50,870
and involves many people.

191
00:08:50,870 --> 00:08:53,080
Director Yu has been transferred
because of this.

192
00:08:53,080 --> 00:08:53,890
What about me?

193
00:08:54,630 --> 00:08:55,790
The bureau has decided

194
00:08:55,790 --> 00:08:57,790
to give you a verbal warning

195
00:08:58,750 --> 00:09:00,680
without putting it in your record.

196
00:09:00,680 --> 00:09:03,020
Your file will be transferred
to the talent exchange center.

197
00:09:03,020 --> 00:09:03,820
Director Jin,

198
00:09:04,000 --> 00:09:05,790
I didn't do anything wrong.

199
00:09:05,790 --> 00:09:06,750
I was just fulfilling

200
00:09:06,750 --> 00:09:08,170
my job responsibilities.

201
00:09:08,170 --> 00:09:10,890
Could you please
speak to the leadership for me?

202
00:09:12,760 --> 00:09:14,520
You're already very lucky.

203
00:09:14,790 --> 00:09:16,480
Just getting a verbal warning

204
00:09:16,480 --> 00:09:17,660
without it going in your record.

205
00:09:17,660 --> 00:09:20,150
This is the greatest protection
we can offer you.

206
00:09:20,150 --> 00:09:21,610
You should appreciate it.

207
00:09:24,750 --> 00:09:27,210
My file being transferred
to the talent exchange center,

208
00:09:27,210 --> 00:09:28,340
what does that mean?

209
00:09:28,740 --> 00:09:29,650
Does it mean

210
00:09:29,800 --> 00:09:32,090
I have to find a new job?

211
00:09:32,240 --> 00:09:35,700
It means your employment
is no longer with the Textile Bureau.

212
00:09:39,770 --> 00:09:41,170
[Distillery Hiring]

213
00:09:41,200 --> 00:09:42,670
[Perfect Innovation]

214
00:09:42,690 --> 00:09:43,770
[Hiring]

215
00:09:45,670 --> 00:09:46,920
[Shibang Foreign Trade Co. Hiring]

216
00:09:51,240 --> 00:09:54,020
[Shanghai Talent Market]

217
00:10:12,360 --> 00:10:13,160
Ye Xining?

218
00:10:14,160 --> 00:10:14,950
Xue Feng?

219
00:10:14,970 --> 00:10:15,780
What?

220
00:10:15,810 --> 00:10:18,010
Your Textile Bureau is recruiting too?

221
00:10:18,900 --> 00:10:20,030
I've heard about it.

222
00:10:20,200 --> 00:10:22,370
You must be getting promoted now.

223
00:10:22,490 --> 00:10:23,750
Section chief, right?

224
00:10:24,390 --> 00:10:26,320
You've risen faster
than anyone in our class.

225
00:10:26,320 --> 00:10:27,360
Share some tips.

226
00:10:27,910 --> 00:10:29,700
I don't really have any tips.

227
00:10:29,870 --> 00:10:31,080
I've been laid off.

228
00:10:31,590 --> 00:10:32,240
Wait.

229
00:10:32,430 --> 00:10:34,440
I just heard you
got promoted a few days ago.

230
00:10:34,440 --> 00:10:36,100
How are you suddenly laid off?

231
00:10:36,510 --> 00:10:38,150
It's complicated.

232
00:10:38,270 --> 00:10:39,810
In a few days it'll be in the newspapers

233
00:10:39,810 --> 00:10:40,810
and you'll see.

234
00:10:41,850 --> 00:10:43,020
So you're

235
00:10:43,120 --> 00:10:44,520
a public figure now, huh?

236
00:10:45,160 --> 00:10:47,920
I see you're looking for
foreign language majors.

237
00:10:47,920 --> 00:10:49,520
Your company's recruiting?

238
00:10:50,820 --> 00:10:51,390
Yes.

239
00:10:52,630 --> 00:10:53,630
You know what?

240
00:10:53,780 --> 00:10:56,030
You'd actually be quite suitable

241
00:10:56,050 --> 00:10:57,200
for our work here.

242
00:10:59,390 --> 00:11:00,390
Let me introduce:

243
00:11:00,600 --> 00:11:01,640
our company

244
00:11:01,800 --> 00:11:03,170
is planning to build

245
00:11:03,200 --> 00:11:05,670
the most modern and luxurious
landmark hotel in Shanghai.

246
00:11:05,670 --> 00:11:06,890
High-level talents like you

247
00:11:06,890 --> 00:11:08,150
are welcome to join us.

248
00:11:08,750 --> 00:11:09,550
Manager Xue,

249
00:11:10,150 --> 00:11:12,350
I was quite interested by what you said.

250
00:11:12,630 --> 00:11:13,790
If I apply now,

251
00:11:13,810 --> 00:11:15,200
what position could I take?

252
00:11:15,200 --> 00:11:17,120
That depends on what you want.

253
00:11:17,120 --> 00:11:18,080
We're currently hiring

254
00:11:18,080 --> 00:11:19,540
for department managers.

255
00:11:19,720 --> 00:11:20,600
But

256
00:11:20,780 --> 00:11:22,310
with your qualifications,

257
00:11:22,480 --> 00:11:24,750
I actually think you're
better suited for...

258
00:11:24,750 --> 00:11:25,550
What?

259
00:11:27,320 --> 00:11:28,480
Executive secretary,

260
00:11:28,480 --> 00:11:29,140
assistant,

261
00:11:29,150 --> 00:11:30,560
personal interpreter and such.

262
00:11:30,560 --> 00:11:31,600
These positions

263
00:11:31,670 --> 00:11:33,600
all require elegant, refined women

264
00:11:33,600 --> 00:11:34,840
with good manners.

265
00:11:35,600 --> 00:11:37,200
Why don't you think about it?

266
00:11:37,320 --> 00:11:39,270
These jobs I recommend
is actually pretty good.

267
00:11:39,270 --> 00:11:40,030
Just think about it.

268
00:11:40,030 --> 00:11:41,390
As an executive secretary or assistant,

269
00:11:41,390 --> 00:11:42,360
after work every day,

270
00:11:42,360 --> 00:11:44,090
you'll accompany the boss to fancy places,

271
00:11:44,090 --> 00:11:45,510
broaden your horizons and see the world.

272
00:11:45,510 --> 00:11:46,510
Isn't that great?

273
00:11:46,550 --> 00:11:48,010
What's so good about that?

274
00:11:48,240 --> 00:11:49,960
What if some big boss
takes a liking to you?

275
00:11:49,960 --> 00:11:52,160
Wouldn't that be a shortcut to success?

276
00:11:53,030 --> 00:11:54,360
Is this how you

277
00:11:54,380 --> 00:11:55,980
recruit all your employees?

278
00:11:56,460 --> 00:11:57,190
Yeah.

279
00:11:57,210 --> 00:11:58,360
If the boss is happy,

280
00:11:58,510 --> 00:11:59,870
then I've done my job.

281
00:12:00,440 --> 00:12:02,840
Then this job really
isn't suitable for me.

282
00:12:03,400 --> 00:12:04,750
It's hard to get by these days.

283
00:12:04,750 --> 00:12:05,840
Why don't you reconsider?

284
00:12:05,840 --> 00:12:07,170
I'll go look elsewhere.

285
00:12:07,200 --> 00:12:07,930
Alright.

286
00:12:07,960 --> 00:12:09,030
Whenever you change your mind,

287
00:12:09,030 --> 00:12:10,430
feel free to come find me.

288
00:12:23,360 --> 00:12:24,290
Xiang Beichuan.

289
00:12:24,960 --> 00:12:26,620
Are you also looking for a job?

290
00:12:26,980 --> 00:12:27,790
Miss Ye,

291
00:12:29,090 --> 00:12:30,080
what are you doing here?

292
00:12:30,080 --> 00:12:31,200
I'm also looking for a job.

293
00:12:31,200 --> 00:12:32,450
Didn't I tell you last time?

294
00:12:32,450 --> 00:12:33,650
It's not optimistic.

295
00:12:34,750 --> 00:12:35,860
So, have you found one?

296
00:12:35,860 --> 00:12:36,860
Not yet.

297
00:12:38,140 --> 00:12:39,470
Did you offend someone?

298
00:12:40,080 --> 00:12:41,910
There's a guy behind you staring at you

299
00:12:41,910 --> 00:12:42,790
and smirking.

300
00:12:46,160 --> 00:12:46,890
You know him?

301
00:12:52,870 --> 00:12:53,870
Professor Xiang,

302
00:12:54,120 --> 00:12:55,670
I've been watching you.

303
00:12:56,000 --> 00:12:56,790
You've been to 7 or 8 places.

304
00:12:56,790 --> 00:12:58,830
How does it feel to be refused repeatedly?

305
00:12:58,830 --> 00:12:59,710
Cut the crap.

306
00:13:00,050 --> 00:13:01,250
Get me a soda quickly.

307
00:13:01,370 --> 00:13:02,350
I'm dying of thirst.

308
00:13:02,350 --> 00:13:03,240
When you left my place,

309
00:13:03,240 --> 00:13:04,150
didn't you take a bunch?

310
00:13:04,150 --> 00:13:05,200
I finished them.

311
00:13:05,480 --> 00:13:06,080
Hurry up.

312
00:13:07,910 --> 00:13:08,510
Here.

313
00:13:09,440 --> 00:13:10,440
I want a new one.

314
00:13:20,560 --> 00:13:21,130
Miss,

315
00:13:21,350 --> 00:13:22,060
have a soda.

316
00:13:22,190 --> 00:13:22,980
Thank you.

317
00:13:25,130 --> 00:13:26,480
You're here job-hunting too?

318
00:13:26,480 --> 00:13:27,200
Yes, I am.

319
00:13:27,450 --> 00:13:28,900
Let me introduce myself.

320
00:13:30,470 --> 00:13:33,030
Xiang Beichuan and I
were college classmates.

321
00:13:33,030 --> 00:13:33,630
Hello.

322
00:13:33,650 --> 00:13:34,380
Hello.

323
00:13:34,490 --> 00:13:35,490
Although we were classmates,

324
00:13:35,490 --> 00:13:37,420
there are differences between us.

325
00:13:38,720 --> 00:13:40,190
I'm the boss of this company.

326
00:13:40,190 --> 00:13:41,470
I'm here today

327
00:13:41,540 --> 00:13:42,870
to recruit people,

328
00:13:43,240 --> 00:13:44,120
while he's here

329
00:13:44,140 --> 00:13:45,140
to apply for a job.

330
00:13:46,370 --> 00:13:47,840
But he does have his strengths.

331
00:13:47,840 --> 00:13:49,480
For example, when we were in school,

332
00:13:49,480 --> 00:13:51,370
his grades were slightly better than mine.

333
00:13:51,370 --> 00:13:52,300
Other than that,

334
00:13:52,670 --> 00:13:55,400
I'm probably better than him
in everything else.

335
00:13:56,550 --> 00:13:57,670
Our company

336
00:13:58,080 --> 00:13:59,550
is a foreign trade business.

337
00:13:59,550 --> 00:14:01,550
We deal with light industrial
imports and exports

338
00:14:01,550 --> 00:14:03,000
and also some pet trade.

339
00:14:03,410 --> 00:14:05,140
We currently need a secretary.

340
00:14:05,670 --> 00:14:06,860
Are you interested, miss?

341
00:14:06,860 --> 00:14:07,650
Secretary?

342
00:14:09,150 --> 00:14:11,670
Does that mean
I'd have to accompany the boss

343
00:14:11,880 --> 00:14:13,360
for meals, drinks,
and business entertainment?

344
00:14:13,360 --> 00:14:14,150
Can you hold your liquor?

345
00:14:14,150 --> 00:14:15,320
I can't drink much.

346
00:14:15,520 --> 00:14:16,760
I get rowdy and talk nonsense

347
00:14:16,760 --> 00:14:17,960
when I drink too much.

348
00:14:19,200 --> 00:14:20,240
Beichuan, see you.

349
00:14:20,240 --> 00:14:21,100
I'm leaving now.

350
00:14:21,100 --> 00:14:22,160
Thank you, Mr. Yan.

351
00:14:30,310 --> 00:14:31,040
What?

352
00:14:31,230 --> 00:14:32,290
What are you doing?

353
00:14:32,910 --> 00:14:35,700
You can't take your eyes
off a pretty girl, can you?

354
00:14:35,700 --> 00:14:36,960
Bros before hoes, man.

355
00:14:38,600 --> 00:14:40,000
Let me ask you something.

356
00:14:40,270 --> 00:14:41,510
In that company of yours,

357
00:14:41,510 --> 00:14:42,320
besides me,

358
00:14:42,320 --> 00:14:43,630
is there anyone else?

359
00:14:44,590 --> 00:14:46,000
You need a secretary?

360
00:14:47,270 --> 00:14:49,100
I think what you need isn't a secretary,

361
00:14:49,100 --> 00:14:50,250
but a girlfriend.

362
00:14:50,480 --> 00:14:51,270
Come on.

363
00:14:52,790 --> 00:14:53,840
Don't you think that girl

364
00:14:53,840 --> 00:14:55,150
is really pretty?

365
00:14:56,320 --> 00:14:57,200
Long hair,

366
00:14:57,430 --> 00:14:58,280
big curls,

367
00:14:58,300 --> 00:14:59,140
fair skin—

368
00:14:59,750 --> 00:15:01,600
I can't help staring
when I see girls like that.

369
00:15:01,600 --> 00:15:03,270
Hurry up and get me a soda.

370
00:15:03,360 --> 00:15:04,200
You hear me?

371
00:15:07,410 --> 00:15:08,240
Get me a new one.

372
00:15:08,240 --> 00:15:10,240
She hasn't had a sip. I was watching.

373
00:15:14,100 --> 00:15:16,500
How does that girl have
such perfect teeth?

374
00:15:24,360 --> 00:15:25,150
Miss Ye.

375
00:15:27,080 --> 00:15:28,030
Mr. Lu.

376
00:15:28,440 --> 00:15:28,910
Let's go.

377
00:15:28,910 --> 00:15:29,840
Let's sit down somewhere.

378
00:15:29,840 --> 00:15:31,120
I'll buy you a coffee.

379
00:15:31,540 --> 00:15:32,020
Sure.

380
00:15:32,050 --> 00:15:32,580
Let's go.

381
00:15:36,720 --> 00:15:37,650
Watch your step.

382
00:15:38,180 --> 00:15:38,690
Come.

383
00:15:42,400 --> 00:15:43,060
Let me do it.

384
00:15:43,280 --> 00:15:44,830
Don't worry, it won't spill.

385
00:15:44,830 --> 00:15:45,490
Have a seat.

386
00:15:50,000 --> 00:15:50,790
Thanks.

387
00:15:54,120 --> 00:15:54,910
Miss Ye,

388
00:15:55,450 --> 00:15:56,790
long time no see.

389
00:15:56,810 --> 00:15:57,840
It's been a while.

390
00:15:57,870 --> 00:15:59,200
Didn't expect to run into you today.

391
00:15:59,200 --> 00:15:59,750
Yes.

392
00:15:59,750 --> 00:16:01,350
I'm so happy to see you today.

393
00:16:02,650 --> 00:16:03,650
Let me update you.

394
00:16:04,750 --> 00:16:06,270
Our state-owned factory

395
00:16:07,780 --> 00:16:09,310
eventually went bankrupt.

396
00:16:10,200 --> 00:16:11,320
But I took out a loan

397
00:16:11,630 --> 00:16:13,320
and bought the factory back.

398
00:16:13,440 --> 00:16:14,960
Together with our workers,

399
00:16:14,960 --> 00:16:16,490
we're doing quite well now.

400
00:16:17,560 --> 00:16:19,020
Since I ran into you today,

401
00:16:19,310 --> 00:16:21,080
I'd like to invite you to our company.

402
00:16:21,080 --> 00:16:22,250
Let's make it bigger

403
00:16:22,320 --> 00:16:23,650
and stronger together.

404
00:16:25,480 --> 00:16:26,270
Mr. Lu,

405
00:16:27,570 --> 00:16:29,600
there's something you might not know.

406
00:16:29,600 --> 00:16:31,750
I've just been fired from my job.

407
00:16:32,100 --> 00:16:33,970
And do you know what
they're saying about me?

408
00:16:33,970 --> 00:16:35,550
They're all saying I neglected my duties.

409
00:16:35,550 --> 00:16:38,400
Right now I've got
no government resources, no connections.

410
00:16:38,400 --> 00:16:40,150
I can't help you with anything anymore.

411
00:16:40,150 --> 00:16:41,320
I heard about it.

412
00:16:42,180 --> 00:16:43,410
It wasn't your fault.

413
00:16:44,270 --> 00:16:45,390
You were wronged.

414
00:16:46,600 --> 00:16:48,800
Those leaders of yours are just idiots.

415
00:16:50,870 --> 00:16:52,400
But it's still a big impact.

416
00:16:53,550 --> 00:16:54,320
Yes.

417
00:16:54,630 --> 00:16:56,480
I used to work in the system too.

418
00:16:57,870 --> 00:16:59,750
I really understand how you feel.

419
00:17:00,750 --> 00:17:02,610
Suddenly losing your secure job,

420
00:17:02,650 --> 00:17:03,740
you must feel

421
00:17:04,060 --> 00:17:04,819
wronged

422
00:17:05,710 --> 00:17:06,710
and lost.

423
00:17:07,510 --> 00:17:08,640
So we're planning

424
00:17:08,829 --> 00:17:10,430
to invite you to our company.

425
00:17:10,839 --> 00:17:12,190
2,000 yuan per month

426
00:17:12,640 --> 00:17:13,640
plus commission.

427
00:17:13,640 --> 00:17:14,640
What do you think?

428
00:17:16,470 --> 00:17:18,400
That's too much. I...

429
00:17:18,420 --> 00:17:19,660
What would I even

430
00:17:19,690 --> 00:17:20,609
do there?

431
00:17:20,630 --> 00:17:21,630
It's not too much.

432
00:17:26,290 --> 00:17:26,890
Well,

433
00:17:28,640 --> 00:17:29,590
back when

434
00:17:30,310 --> 00:17:31,350
our factory was

435
00:17:31,400 --> 00:17:33,330
going through its toughest times,

436
00:17:33,550 --> 00:17:34,410
you were the one

437
00:17:35,030 --> 00:17:36,030
who helped us out.

438
00:17:37,690 --> 00:17:39,550
All of us remember your kindness.

439
00:17:39,750 --> 00:17:41,080
No, Mr. Lu,

440
00:17:41,830 --> 00:17:44,030
I really appreciate your invitation

441
00:17:44,030 --> 00:17:44,710
and

442
00:17:44,730 --> 00:17:46,770
offering me 2,000 yuan per month.

443
00:17:47,960 --> 00:17:49,440
But if this is the reason,

444
00:17:49,440 --> 00:17:50,200
if you want to

445
00:17:50,200 --> 00:17:52,130
help me when I'm at my lowest point,

446
00:17:52,200 --> 00:17:53,750
I think it's really unfair to you,

447
00:17:53,750 --> 00:17:55,480
and I don't accept this kind of pity.

448
00:17:55,480 --> 00:17:56,240
No, no, no.

449
00:17:56,740 --> 00:17:58,540
I must have explained it poorly.

450
00:17:59,110 --> 00:18:00,750
We actually value

451
00:18:00,790 --> 00:18:02,730
your professional skills, Miss Ye.

452
00:18:02,730 --> 00:18:04,100
We've seen it.

453
00:18:04,880 --> 00:18:05,880
You majored

454
00:18:06,000 --> 00:18:07,630
in foreign languages, right?

455
00:18:07,630 --> 00:18:08,430
Yes.

456
00:18:08,510 --> 00:18:09,480
Our company is now

457
00:18:09,480 --> 00:18:11,240
about to expand into international trade.

458
00:18:11,240 --> 00:18:13,480
Foreign language talents
are exactly what we need most.

459
00:18:13,480 --> 00:18:14,790
Look at you, you're beautiful,

460
00:18:14,790 --> 00:18:15,110
aren't you?

461
00:18:15,110 --> 00:18:16,790
And you have excellent
interpersonal skills.

462
00:18:16,790 --> 00:18:17,640
If you join our company,

463
00:18:17,640 --> 00:18:19,970
you'll definitely be like a fish in water.

464
00:18:21,290 --> 00:18:22,010
Alright.

465
00:18:22,040 --> 00:18:22,770
Then I'll...

466
00:18:23,950 --> 00:18:25,000
I'll think about it.

467
00:18:25,000 --> 00:18:25,480
Good.

468
00:18:26,000 --> 00:18:27,610
Then it's settled for now.

469
00:18:27,640 --> 00:18:29,070
I haven't decided yet.

470
00:18:29,960 --> 00:18:30,640
Cheers.

471
00:18:38,310 --> 00:18:39,170
Here. Tissues.

472
00:18:39,720 --> 00:18:40,680
It's so hot!

473
00:18:48,440 --> 00:18:50,900
Based on your accommodation requirements,

474
00:18:50,920 --> 00:18:52,340
the room doesn't need to be big,

475
00:18:52,340 --> 00:18:53,650
close to the company,

476
00:18:54,610 --> 00:18:56,140
and preferably rent-free.

477
00:18:56,770 --> 00:18:57,590
I think you'll definitely

478
00:18:57,590 --> 00:18:58,550
like this place.

479
00:19:02,830 --> 00:19:03,560
Are we there?

480
00:19:03,770 --> 00:19:04,450
Yes.

481
00:19:05,070 --> 00:19:06,500
Our company is just
around the corner to the right.

482
00:19:06,500 --> 00:19:07,360
So convenient.

483
00:19:19,530 --> 00:19:20,380
A hair salon?

484
00:19:25,400 --> 00:19:26,030
Wait,

485
00:19:26,490 --> 00:19:27,350
they're still open for business.

486
00:19:27,350 --> 00:19:29,350
It's not appropriate
for me to live here, is it?

487
00:19:29,350 --> 00:19:30,950
They operate during the day.

488
00:19:31,720 --> 00:19:32,790
So you mean

489
00:19:33,350 --> 00:19:35,410
during the day I work at your company,

490
00:19:35,590 --> 00:19:36,880
and at night after they close,

491
00:19:36,880 --> 00:19:37,750
I live here?

492
00:19:40,890 --> 00:19:42,420
Try laying that chair flat.

493
00:19:42,440 --> 00:19:44,640
It's very comfy to lie on. I've tried it.

494
00:19:45,350 --> 00:19:46,110
Try it.

495
00:19:47,200 --> 00:19:48,000
This...

496
00:19:48,640 --> 00:19:49,440
Mr. Su.

497
00:19:50,440 --> 00:19:51,000
Mr. Yan.

498
00:19:51,000 --> 00:19:51,880
He's the owner.

499
00:19:51,900 --> 00:19:52,350
Hello.

500
00:19:52,350 --> 00:19:52,960
Hello.

501
00:19:52,960 --> 00:19:53,200
Hello.

502
00:19:53,200 --> 00:19:55,090
When your hair's long,
he can cut it for you.

503
00:19:55,090 --> 00:19:55,630
Anytime.

504
00:19:55,650 --> 00:19:56,200
Anytime.

505
00:19:57,220 --> 00:19:57,980
Go try it.

506
00:19:58,230 --> 00:19:59,160
Try it.

507
00:20:00,160 --> 00:20:00,960
Busy?

508
00:20:01,360 --> 00:20:02,270
Please go on.

509
00:20:02,400 --> 00:20:03,050
Alright.

510
00:20:09,640 --> 00:20:11,240
Your shop is quite spacious.

511
00:20:11,260 --> 00:20:12,190
It's okay.

512
00:20:12,210 --> 00:20:13,140
Just a small one.

513
00:20:17,240 --> 00:20:18,000
Idiot.

514
00:20:18,350 --> 00:20:19,030
Idiot.

515
00:20:20,550 --> 00:20:21,350
This way.

516
00:20:32,270 --> 00:20:34,470
This place is our company's warehouse.

517
00:20:34,580 --> 00:20:35,710
But the good point is

518
00:20:36,480 --> 00:20:37,270
it's quiet at night.

519
00:20:37,270 --> 00:20:39,270
You said you wanted to write, right?

520
00:20:40,030 --> 00:20:40,750
And if you need

521
00:20:40,750 --> 00:20:42,350
anything else,

522
00:20:42,370 --> 00:20:42,960
just...

523
00:20:42,990 --> 00:20:44,160
just let me know.

524
00:20:45,280 --> 00:20:46,040
Is this place

525
00:20:46,070 --> 00:20:46,920
okay with you?

526
00:20:47,110 --> 00:20:47,780
Yes.

527
00:20:48,700 --> 00:20:50,760
This place is better than over there.

528
00:20:51,350 --> 00:20:52,640
And you helped me pay back

529
00:20:52,640 --> 00:20:54,480
that 60,000 yuan to the university.

530
00:20:54,480 --> 00:20:55,810
I still owe you for that.

531
00:20:58,160 --> 00:20:59,240
The bed and desk you mentioned

532
00:20:59,240 --> 00:21:00,000
are all here.

533
00:21:00,720 --> 00:21:01,310
If you get hot,

534
00:21:01,310 --> 00:21:02,240
there's a fan.

535
00:21:02,960 --> 00:21:03,680
Try it out.

536
00:21:03,710 --> 00:21:04,550
It might not work well.

537
00:21:04,550 --> 00:21:05,290
If it shorts out,

538
00:21:05,290 --> 00:21:06,030
stop using it immediately.

539
00:21:06,030 --> 00:21:07,830
Tell me and I'll buy you a new one.

540
00:21:09,340 --> 00:21:10,320
As for the rest...

541
00:21:10,320 --> 00:21:11,320
Let me help you tidy up.

542
00:21:11,320 --> 00:21:12,030
No need.

543
00:21:12,060 --> 00:21:13,060
Really, don't bother.

544
00:21:13,060 --> 00:21:14,590
You go ahead with your work.

545
00:21:15,550 --> 00:21:17,950
Alright then,
I'll head back to the office.

546
00:21:18,370 --> 00:21:19,830
You can manage on your own.

547
00:21:20,200 --> 00:21:21,090
Thanks a lot.

548
00:21:54,860 --> 00:21:55,830
I've signed in downstairs.

549
00:21:55,830 --> 00:21:56,000
[Shanghai Textile Industry Bureau]

550
00:21:56,000 --> 00:21:57,400
I'm here to get my things.

551
00:22:08,480 --> 00:22:09,270
Xining,

552
00:22:09,550 --> 00:22:10,810
you're leaving today?

553
00:22:12,180 --> 00:22:13,660
What a pity.

554
00:22:14,550 --> 00:22:16,310
Look, for ordinary things
worth a hundred or so,

555
00:22:16,310 --> 00:22:18,270
you're always so precise
with the accounts.

556
00:22:18,270 --> 00:22:19,350
But when it comes to Huang Yahui,

557
00:22:19,350 --> 00:22:20,880
you suddenly got confused?

558
00:22:23,360 --> 00:22:24,160
Ms. Wang,

559
00:22:24,550 --> 00:22:26,960
that American jeans agent
you mentioned last time,

560
00:22:26,960 --> 00:22:27,830
what was the name?

561
00:22:27,830 --> 00:22:28,790
S... what?

562
00:22:28,980 --> 00:22:29,740
What's up?

563
00:22:30,270 --> 00:22:32,150
Director Jin has his eye
on the 5,000-piece

564
00:22:32,150 --> 00:22:33,640
premium jeans order.

565
00:22:33,680 --> 00:22:35,280
Have you followed up on that?

566
00:22:35,790 --> 00:22:37,790
His terms are too harsh.

567
00:22:37,790 --> 00:22:39,400
We need to negotiate with him further.

568
00:22:39,400 --> 00:22:40,930
All the materials are here.

569
00:22:41,480 --> 00:22:42,270
Get on it.

570
00:22:42,270 --> 00:22:42,960
I know.

571
00:22:44,750 --> 00:22:45,440
By the way,

572
00:22:45,620 --> 00:22:46,680
don't you also think now

573
00:22:46,680 --> 00:22:48,570
that Huang Yahui is pretty disgusting?

574
00:22:48,570 --> 00:22:50,070
You were always so good to her,

575
00:22:50,070 --> 00:22:51,470
yet she still harmed you.

576
00:22:51,470 --> 00:22:53,190
She's truly heartless.

577
00:22:53,350 --> 00:22:54,590
When you're out in the society,

578
00:22:54,590 --> 00:22:57,250
you better be more careful
when judging people.

579
00:22:58,240 --> 00:22:58,960
Sis.

580
00:22:59,500 --> 00:23:01,430
