00:32:22,480 --> 00:32:23,000
Pick one

874
00:32:23,000 --> 00:32:24,170
that you want to sleep in.

875
00:32:24,170 --> 00:32:24,900
Is that okay?

876
00:32:25,360 --> 00:32:26,760
Come on, pick one.

877
00:32:27,620 --> 00:32:28,220
Let's go.

878
00:32:28,960 --> 00:32:30,160
Sorry about earlier.

879
00:32:31,280 --> 00:32:31,920
Come on, you pick.

880
00:32:31,920 --> 00:32:33,130
Which of these two beds do you like?

881
00:32:33,130 --> 00:32:33,720
You pick.

882
00:32:34,030 --> 00:32:34,830
Is it my pick?

883
00:32:34,850 --> 00:32:36,240
It's your pick, go on.

884
00:32:36,270 --> 00:32:36,940
Whichever one you pick,

885
00:32:36,940 --> 00:32:38,080
I'll take the other one.

886
00:32:38,080 --> 00:32:39,410
I'll take this one then.

887
00:32:40,440 --> 00:32:41,970
That's the one I wanted too.

888
00:32:47,660 --> 00:32:50,290
Do you know who slept in this bed before?

889
00:32:50,640 --> 00:32:51,310
Who?

890
00:32:51,680 --> 00:32:53,280
The embezzler you were
talking about just now.

891
00:32:53,280 --> 00:32:54,310
Her name is Huang Yahui.

892
00:32:54,310 --> 00:32:55,660
She used to lie right here.

893
00:32:55,660 --> 00:32:56,880
Oh my god! That's terrifying.

894
00:32:56,880 --> 00:32:57,900
I won't sleep in this one then.

895
00:32:57,900 --> 00:32:59,100
You can have it to yourself.

896
00:32:59,100 --> 00:33:00,510
Then you sleep there.
You two get along well.

897
00:33:00,510 --> 00:33:01,470
You have a good relationship.

898
00:33:01,470 --> 00:33:03,230
I'll make do with this one.

899
00:33:04,060 --> 00:33:05,060
This one suits me.

900
00:33:05,550 --> 00:33:06,400
Are you sure?

901
00:33:07,350 --> 00:33:08,150
Yes, I'm sure.

902
00:33:08,320 --> 00:33:09,200
Not changing anymore?

903
00:33:09,200 --> 00:33:10,570
Not changing, I guess.

904
00:33:10,650 --> 00:33:12,650
Alright then. I'll get back to work.

905
00:33:17,030 --> 00:33:18,290
So you'll sleep there?

906
00:33:18,920 --> 00:33:20,240
Then I'll make the bed.

907
00:33:21,640 --> 00:33:22,970
Don't change your mind.

908
00:33:49,000 --> 00:33:50,640
That girl who was with you
at the job fair,

909
00:33:50,640 --> 00:33:51,570
whose name is...

910
00:33:51,590 --> 00:33:52,350
Ye...

911
00:33:52,400 --> 00:33:53,000
Ye Xining.

912
00:33:53,000 --> 00:33:53,930
Yes, that's her.

913
00:33:54,720 --> 00:33:56,920
She went to work at Lu Guoyao's company.

914
00:33:58,000 --> 00:33:58,880
I know.

915
00:33:59,520 --> 00:34:00,960
I just ran into her.

916
00:34:02,720 --> 00:34:04,400
That old fox Lu Guoyao.

917
00:34:04,490 --> 00:34:06,020
He's messing with my plans.

918
00:34:07,180 --> 00:34:09,040
How is he messing with your plans?

919
00:34:10,630 --> 00:34:12,440
A girl that good-looking

920
00:34:12,639 --> 00:34:13,929
is worth considering.

921
00:34:15,320 --> 00:34:16,650
Are you sick in the head?

922
00:34:17,300 --> 00:34:18,760
You should get treatment.

923
00:34:21,190 --> 00:34:22,550
If the child takes after her,

924
00:34:22,550 --> 00:34:24,440
he or she will be very beautiful.

925
00:34:25,480 --> 00:34:26,510
For sure.

926
00:34:28,760 --> 00:34:30,290
Time to take your medicine.

927
00:34:32,360 --> 00:34:34,020
I definitely can't let her go.

928
00:34:34,830 --> 00:34:37,060
Mr. Yan, who are you feuding with?

929
00:34:42,550 --> 00:34:43,110
Hello.

930
00:34:43,110 --> 00:34:45,590
Hello. Is Mr. Li in?

931
00:34:46,139 --> 00:34:47,540
Mr. Li has stepped out.

932
00:34:47,630 --> 00:34:49,030
When will he be back?

933
00:34:49,800 --> 00:34:50,590
I don't know.

934
00:34:51,909 --> 00:34:53,830
Can I wait for him here?

935
00:34:54,230 --> 00:34:54,790
Sure.

936
00:34:54,810 --> 00:34:55,530
Thank you.

937
00:35:02,410 --> 00:35:10,500
[Xinda Clothing Foreign Trade Company]

938
00:35:26,710 --> 00:35:27,390
Hello.

939
00:35:27,910 --> 00:35:29,240
I'm about to leave work.

940
00:35:29,280 --> 00:35:30,840
Could you give me your card?

941
00:35:30,920 --> 00:35:32,630
Once I schedule a time with Mr. Li,

942
00:35:32,630 --> 00:35:34,030
I'll call to let you know.

943
00:35:34,380 --> 00:35:36,350
Let me write down my phone number for you.

944
00:35:36,350 --> 00:35:37,100
Okay.

945
00:35:39,830 --> 00:35:41,030
You can write it here.

946
00:35:44,030 --> 00:35:45,200
Zhou, this is...

947
00:35:45,230 --> 00:35:46,020
Mr. Li.

948
00:35:46,840 --> 00:35:47,630
Ye?

949
00:35:47,630 --> 00:35:48,280
Mr. Li.

950
00:35:48,280 --> 00:35:49,610
What are you doing here?

951
00:35:50,670 --> 00:35:52,320
About that order for premium jeans

952
00:35:52,320 --> 00:35:53,840
that you want to produce,

953
00:35:54,070 --> 00:35:56,200
I'd like to have a proper talk with you.

954
00:35:58,100 --> 00:35:59,240
Let's talk in my office.

955
00:35:59,240 --> 00:35:59,760
Okay.

956
00:35:59,790 --> 00:36:00,250
Let's go.

957
00:36:00,250 --> 00:36:01,450
You're free to go now.

958
00:36:03,910 --> 00:36:04,770
Please come in.

959
00:36:06,510 --> 00:36:07,170
Have a seat.

960
00:36:13,400 --> 00:36:14,110
Mr. Li.

961
00:36:14,800 --> 00:36:17,000
I heard you have an urgent order

962
00:36:17,150 --> 00:36:18,400
that needs to be completed within a month,

963
00:36:18,400 --> 00:36:20,760
producing 5,000 pairs of high-end jeans.

964
00:36:21,280 --> 00:36:23,300
And the craftsmanship requirements
are also very high.

965
00:36:23,300 --> 00:36:24,780
I happen to know a factory

966
00:36:24,840 --> 00:36:27,570
that I believe
can fully meet your requirements.

967
00:36:28,790 --> 00:36:29,620
Ye.

968
00:36:30,320 --> 00:36:32,450
This order has never been made public.

969
00:36:32,850 --> 00:36:34,450
How did you find out about it?

970
00:36:34,990 --> 00:36:35,800
Mr. Li.

971
00:36:36,140 --> 00:36:37,750
Our industry is quite small.

972
00:36:45,630 --> 00:36:46,360
Mr. Li.

973
00:36:46,720 --> 00:36:48,860
I completely understand your concerns.

974
00:36:48,860 --> 00:36:49,420
Although I've

975
00:36:49,420 --> 00:36:51,070
left the factory,

976
00:36:51,170 --> 00:36:52,360
I don't think that affects

977
00:36:52,360 --> 00:36:54,890
the quality of work
this factory can produce.

978
00:36:56,010 --> 00:36:56,820
Ye,

979
00:36:58,280 --> 00:36:59,150
to be honest,

980
00:36:59,510 --> 00:37:01,840
we already have manufacturing partners.

981
00:37:01,910 --> 00:37:02,440
And actually,

982
00:37:02,440 --> 00:37:04,400
we've almost finalized an agreement

983
00:37:04,400 --> 00:37:05,660
with another factory.

984
00:37:06,170 --> 00:37:08,500
We've worked with them many times before.

985
00:37:08,750 --> 00:37:10,190
The key is that their price

986
00:37:10,190 --> 00:37:11,320
is very reasonable.

987
00:37:11,480 --> 00:37:12,280
I understand.

988
00:37:12,290 --> 00:37:13,420
I completely get it.

989
00:37:13,550 --> 00:37:14,440
If I were in your position,

990
00:37:14,440 --> 00:37:15,590
for stability,

991
00:37:15,590 --> 00:37:18,450
I'd also choose suppliers
I've worked with before.

992
00:37:18,840 --> 00:37:19,630
However,

993
00:37:19,650 --> 00:37:21,780
our advantage lies in our technology.

994
00:37:22,030 --> 00:37:22,960
Our technology

995
00:37:23,080 --> 00:37:24,880
ensures the pre-shrinkage rate of jeans

996
00:37:24,880 --> 00:37:27,280
remains consistently within 2.5%.

997
00:37:27,630 --> 00:37:30,150
This means higher pass rate
for finished garments

998
00:37:30,150 --> 00:37:32,070
and lower return rates later on.

999
00:37:33,060 --> 00:37:33,860
Go on.

1000
00:37:34,440 --> 00:37:35,440
Moreover, our factory

1001
00:37:35,440 --> 00:37:37,960
has imported many German rapier looms

1002
00:37:37,980 --> 00:37:39,510
and Japanese sewing machines.

1003
00:37:39,510 --> 00:37:40,710
With this equipment,

1004
00:37:40,780 --> 00:37:42,700
we can complete orders on time

1005
00:37:42,730 --> 00:37:44,860
while ensuring quality and quantity.

1006
00:37:51,280 --> 00:37:52,070
Ye.

1007
00:37:53,890 --> 00:37:56,100
I must say that what you've described

1008
00:37:56,630 --> 00:37:58,280
is quite appealing to me.

1009
00:37:59,790 --> 00:38:00,920
Here's what I'll do.

1010
00:38:01,010 --> 00:38:03,010
I'll discuss this with my team

1011
00:38:03,550 --> 00:38:04,550
and we'll see

1012
00:38:04,630 --> 00:38:05,480
if we need

1013
00:38:05,480 --> 00:38:07,150
to switch to a new supplier.

1014
00:38:07,560 --> 00:38:08,810
Sure, no problem.

1015
00:38:09,460 --> 00:38:10,270
Mr. Li,

1016
00:38:10,290 --> 00:38:11,730
if you'd like to know more

1017
00:38:11,760 --> 00:38:14,230
or visit our factory
to see the production equipment,

1018
00:38:14,230 --> 00:38:15,340
please contact me anytime.

1019
00:38:15,340 --> 00:38:16,670
We welcome you at any time.

1020
00:38:16,670 --> 00:38:17,150
Okay.

1021
00:38:17,530 --> 00:38:19,010
I'll be in touch.

1022
00:38:19,630 --> 00:38:20,030
Okay.

1023
00:38:20,070 --> 00:38:20,600
Alright.

1024
00:38:23,480 --> 00:38:25,420
While we're fighting, you throw stones.

1025
00:38:25,420 --> 00:38:27,680
While we're fighting, you throw stones.

1026
00:38:27,690 --> 00:38:29,730
How mean can you be?

1027
00:38:30,510 --> 00:38:33,150
You're not sleeping
in the middle of the night,

1028
00:38:33,150 --> 00:38:34,940
burning the midnight oil,

1029
00:38:34,970 --> 00:38:36,810
just to torment people.

1030
00:38:40,560 --> 00:38:42,160
You old swordsman.

1031
00:38:43,320 --> 00:38:44,880
You know quite a lot.

1032
00:38:45,630 --> 00:38:47,470
Let me make myself clear.

1033
00:38:48,990 --> 00:38:50,720
I won't fight over it.

1034
00:38:52,710 --> 00:38:54,310
It's the middle of the night!

1035
00:38:55,220 --> 00:38:55,900
You...

1036
00:38:57,250 --> 00:38:58,040
Jiuling.

1037
00:38:58,910 --> 00:39:00,510
Could you please keep it down?

1038
00:39:00,510 --> 00:39:02,510
I'm still organizing my materials.

1039
00:39:12,920 --> 00:39:14,550
♪ New Year ♪

1040
00:39:15,200 --> 00:39:17,970
♪ The first day ♪

1041
00:39:19,550 --> 00:39:21,070
♪ Reunite ♪

1042
00:39:21,100 --> 00:39:24,220
♪ The young pay
New Year's greetings to the elders ♪

1043
00:39:24,690 --> 00:39:25,430
I switched to another one.

1044
00:39:25,430 --> 00:39:26,560
Do you like this one?

1045
00:39:30,880 --> 00:39:33,770
♪ Wear the new clothes ♪

1046
00:39:36,050 --> 00:39:38,740
♪ Wear the new clothes ♪

1047
00:40:05,840 --> 00:40:06,840
Professor Xiang.

1048
00:40:07,070 --> 00:40:08,000
Still awake?

1049
00:40:08,360 --> 00:40:09,150
Miss Ye.

1050
00:40:09,320 --> 00:40:10,850
May I come in and take a look?

1051
00:40:11,270 --> 00:40:12,800
Miss Ye, it's so late. Uh...

1052
00:40:13,440 --> 00:40:15,190
Your room is really small.

1053
00:40:15,790 --> 00:40:17,230
And so many books.

1054
00:40:19,320 --> 00:40:20,880
Why is there a dog cage?

1055
00:40:21,240 --> 00:40:21,830
Don't tell me

1056
00:40:21,830 --> 00:40:23,630
Mr. Yan makes you live with a dog.

1057
00:40:25,550 --> 00:40:26,400
No.

1058
00:40:26,960 --> 00:40:28,030
Not yet, anyway.

1059
00:40:29,590 --> 00:40:31,360
A grown man like you
sleeping in such a narrow bed.

1060
00:40:31,360 --> 00:40:32,820
It's really unfair to you.

1061
00:40:33,880 --> 00:40:34,670
It's fine.

1062
00:40:34,670 --> 00:40:35,360
Well,

1063
00:40:35,520 --> 00:40:36,670
as long as it's long enough.

1064
00:40:36,670 --> 00:40:37,440
I couldn't handle it.

1065
00:40:37,440 --> 00:40:39,190
I toss and turn a lot when I sleep.

1066
00:40:39,190 --> 00:40:40,230
And when I dream,

1067
00:40:40,230 --> 00:40:41,960
especially when it's a nightmare,
I'd definitely fall off

1068
00:40:41,960 --> 00:40:43,760
and crash right onto this table.

1069
00:40:45,280 --> 00:40:46,590
What are you cooking?

1070
00:40:47,660 --> 00:40:49,080
I got hungry while reading.

1071
00:40:49,080 --> 00:40:50,260
Just cooking some instant noodles...

1072
00:40:50,260 --> 00:40:51,660
I'm actually hungry too.

1073
00:40:51,960 --> 00:40:52,800
I only bought one pack.

1074
00:40:52,800 --> 00:40:54,390
Probably not enough for both of us.

1075
00:40:54,390 --> 00:40:55,350
It's okay.

1076
00:40:55,890 --> 00:40:56,630
I don't eat much.

1077
00:40:56,630 --> 00:40:58,290
Can't I just have half of this?

1078
00:40:58,430 --> 00:40:59,230
Alright.

1079
00:41:02,560 --> 00:41:03,880
Don't sit on that chair.

1080
00:41:03,880 --> 00:41:05,070
You scared me!

1081
00:41:05,360 --> 00:41:06,560
What's wrong with it?

1082
00:41:06,830 --> 00:41:07,920
The screws underneath are loose.

1083
00:41:07,920 --> 00:41:09,180
I haven't fixed it yet.

1084
00:41:10,390 --> 00:41:11,990
If I break it, I'll pay for it.

1085
00:41:12,320 --> 00:41:13,120
That's not it.

1086
00:41:13,590 --> 00:41:15,120
I'm worried if you sit on it,

1087
00:41:15,230 --> 00:41:15,920
you might fall and hurt yourself,

1088
00:41:15,920 --> 00:41:17,710
then I'd have to compensate you.

1089
00:41:17,710 --> 00:41:18,810
You wouldn't need to compensate me.

1090
00:41:18,810 --> 00:41:20,610
I'm already up to my neck in debt.

1091
00:41:20,880 --> 00:41:22,550
Aren't you in debt too?

1092
00:41:24,970 --> 00:41:26,030
Speaking of which,

1093
00:41:26,480 --> 00:41:28,080
we have quite a lot in common.

1094
00:41:28,360 --> 00:41:30,280
Both of us down on our luck.

1095
00:41:31,850 --> 00:41:33,570
But at least that's all behind us now.

1096
00:41:33,570 --> 00:41:35,010
We both found jobs

1097
00:41:35,110 --> 00:41:37,070
and even became neighbors
in this building.

1098
00:41:37,070 --> 00:41:38,950
Shouldn't we celebrate this?

1099
00:41:40,370 --> 00:41:41,210
Celebrate?

1100
00:41:41,300 --> 00:41:42,900
We should toast to this!

1101
00:41:44,280 --> 00:41:45,070
Toast?

1102
00:41:45,180 --> 00:41:46,270
Get a bowl.

1103
00:41:53,800 --> 00:41:54,850
Well, the noodles...

1104
00:41:54,850 --> 00:41:55,730
Serve some.

1105
00:41:57,360 --> 00:41:58,190
Thank you.

1106
00:41:59,550 --> 00:42:00,400
Professor Xiang.

1107
00:42:00,400 --> 00:42:02,230
You're so cultured
with your Chinese literature background.

1108
00:42:02,230 --> 00:42:03,760
Shouldn't you say something profound?

1109
00:42:03,760 --> 00:42:05,360
In Gorky's
"The Song of the Stormy Petrel,"

1110
00:42:05,360 --> 00:42:06,960
there's a line that goes...

1111
00:42:10,030 --> 00:42:10,840
It says,

1112
00:42:12,230 --> 00:42:14,550
when people face life's difficulties,

1113
00:42:15,110 --> 00:42:17,030
they should be like the stormy petrel,

1114
00:42:17,030 --> 00:42:18,430
flying toward the storm,

1115
00:42:18,540 --> 00:42:20,070
and soaring with outstretched wings.

1116
00:42:20,070 --> 00:42:20,800
That's it!

1117
00:42:21,310 --> 00:42:22,690
To us, two stormy petrels!

1118
00:42:22,690 --> 00:42:24,620
Soaring with outstretched wings.

1119
00:42:32,570 --> 00:42:33,300
Delicious.

1120
00:42:38,360 --> 00:42:39,360
Professor Xiang.

1121
00:42:39,860 --> 00:42:41,590
I must say, you're quite brave.

1122
00:42:43,360 --> 00:42:44,400
This kind of stove

1123
00:42:44,610 --> 00:42:45,870
can easily catch fire.

1124
00:42:46,090 --> 00:42:47,560
This room could go up in flames,

1125
00:42:47,560 --> 00:42:49,280
and you could burn down
the whole building.

1126
00:42:49,280 --> 00:42:50,480
That's a bit extreme.

1127
00:42:50,960 --> 00:42:51,960
How is it extreme?

1128
00:42:53,100 --> 00:42:54,430
At our school before,

1129
00:42:55,480 --> 00:42:56,690
because of this type of stove,

1130
00:42:56,690 --> 00:42:57,640
two people died.

1131
00:42:59,190 --> 00:43:01,360
And they were also eating noodles.

1132
00:43:02,840 --> 00:43:04,280
Instant noodles, too.

1133
00:43:05,220 --> 00:43:05,900
One guy

1134
00:43:06,190 --> 00:43:06,920
and one girl.

1135
00:43:07,920 --> 00:43:09,360
The guy was also

1136
00:43:09,360 --> 00:43:11,090
sitting on a bed just like this.

1137
00:43:11,360 --> 00:43:13,480
And the girl had hair
the same length as mine...

1138
00:43:13,480 --> 00:43:14,080
Fine.

1139
00:43:14,100 --> 00:43:14,970
Stop talking. Please stop.

1140
00:43:14,970 --> 00:43:16,300
I'll unplug it right now.
